PREP: CLEAN: Wash hands. Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Combine all ingredients in large slow cooker; mix well. CLEAN: Wash hands. COOK: Cook on low setting at least 6 hours or until internal juices of chicken run clear. (Or insert instant-read meat thermometer in thickest part of chicken. Temperature should read 180 degrees F.) SERVE: Serve over pasta or baked potatoes, if desired. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.